<AcademyLayout
  title="Summer 2026: learn, work, start up with Nguyen AI Edu"
  description="Summer 2026, Nguyen AI Edu opens a series of learning, practice, career orientation, part-time work and startup programs for students nationwide. Online, with in-person experiences in Da Lat."
  activeNav="home"
>
  <article class="academy-container py-12 max-w-3xl">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-academy-text mb-4 leading-tight">
        Summer 2026: Nguyen AI Edu opens a series of learning, work, part-time and startup programs for students nationwide
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-academy-muted">
        A summer for young people to begin building their own path
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-academy">
      <p>
        There are summers meant only for rest. And there are summers that become a turning point.
      </p>

      <p>
        For students about to graduate, those who just graduated, those looking for work, those who want part-time jobs, or those standing before a new choice in their career — summer is not just empty time. It is when a young person can look back at themselves, learn a new capability, try doing something real, find the right environment and begin building their own path.
      </p>

      <p>
        In summer 2026, Nguyen AI Edu opens a series of learning, practice, career orientation, part-time work support, startup support and personal capability development programs for students, young people and anyone who wants to enter the age of artificial intelligence with a more proactive mindset.
      </p>

      <p>
        The program runs online nationwide. Some practice activities, meetups, group learning, project work and experiences will be organized in person in Da Lat, Lam Dong province when scheduling allows.
      </p>

      <p>
        Nguyen AI Edu prioritizes those who carry the Nguyen surname, while welcoming all young people who genuinely love learning, technology, artificial intelligence, creativity, startups, local brands, national brands and who want to create real value for themselves, their families, their communities and society.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>When young people need more than a course</h2>

      <p>
        Many young people today do not lack information. What they lack is an environment that helps them turn information into capability.
      </p>

      <p>
        Some have studied a lot but cannot articulate what they can do. Some want to work but have no product, project or clear capability portfolio. Some want part-time work but want that work to help them grow, not just trade time for short-term income. Some want to start a business but do not know where to begin — which problem, which customers, which product, which brand. Some have heard a lot about artificial intelligence but do not know how to use it as a capability for learning, working and creating responsibly.
      </p>

      <p>
        Nguyen AI Edu was built from that need.
      </p>

      <p>
        Not just learning to know. Not just learning to get a certificate. But learning to do work, to create products, to present capabilities, to see one's path more clearly and to gradually become self-directed in one's career.
      </p>

      <p>
        Education in a new era should not stop at the classroom. Education needs to open up the ability to work, to create, to collaborate, to self-learn and to stand firm in a world that is changing very fast.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Learn to do. Do to understand yourself. Understand yourself to go further.</h2>

      <p>
        The spirit of the summer 2026 program series is learning paired with practice.
      </p>

      <p>
        Learners are guided through each topic, doing exercises, trying work, building a portfolio, creating content, joining small projects, presenting ideas, revising products and recording results step by step.
      </p>

      <p>
        No one necessarily has to start with a big idea. Sometimes a clearer personal portfolio, a better article, a project landing page, a job search plan, a content product, a small research piece, or a coherently presented startup idea is already a worthwhile beginning.
      </p>

      <p>
        What matters is that after the program, learners do not leave with the feeling of "having heard a few more lessons," but hold something that belongs to them: a portfolio, a product, a capability, a direction, or a new connection.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Main learning and practice directions</h2>

      <h3>Artificial intelligence for learning and work</h3>
      <p>
        Learners are guided to use artificial intelligence as a tool to support learning, research, writing, planning, analysis, organizing documents and handling work. The focus is not on chasing new tools, but on asking better questions, checking results more carefully, working more structurally and using AI to enhance genuine human capability.
      </p>

      <h3>Capability portfolio and job search</h3>
      <p>
        A young person entering the labor market needs more than a resume. Nguyen AI Edu guides learners in building a personal capability portfolio: who they are, what they are learning, what they can do, what they have tried, what products they have, what direction they have and where they want to contribute. That portfolio can serve job seeking, internships, part-time work, project collaboration or long-term personal brand building.
      </p>

      <h3>Part-time work, internships and real projects</h3>
      <p>
        Part-time work is not just about earning extra income. If chosen well, part-time work is a way to learn a trade. The program guides learners toward jobs that build real capability: content support, media, research, community care, project assistance, classroom support, business support, program operations, verified data entry and suitable online work. Learners are encouraged to see each job as part of their capability portfolio, not just a temporary gig.
      </p>

      <h3>Content creation and personal brand</h3>
      <p>
        In the digital age, young people need to know how to tell their story clearly, authentically and with value. Not to show off. Not to chase momentary attention. But so that others understand what they are learning, what they are doing, what they care about, what capabilities they have and where collaboration is possible. Nguyen AI Edu guides learners in building content topics, a personal voice, articles, a landing page and a capability journey in an orderly way.
      </p>

      <h3>Local brand, national brand and Vietnamese products</h3>
      <p>
        A young person does not necessarily have to start from something far away. Many values can begin from where they live. Da Lat, Lam Dong, agriculture, tourism, education, culture, local products, family stories, traditional crafts, local communities and Vietnamese values can all become material for building a brand. Nguyen AI Edu encourages learners to observe their locality, find real problems, tell real stories, try small products and learn to turn local value into competitive capability in a new era.
      </p>

      <h3>Small startups and digital business</h3>
      <p>
        A startup does not begin with a slogan. A startup begins with a specific problem, a specific group of people, a product that can be tested and a responsible way of operating. Learners are introduced to foundational steps: understand customers, describe the problem, design a test product, build a landing page, create content, try selling, receive feedback, adjust and refine. The program encourages learners to start small, test for real, go slow but steady, and build a foundation before expanding.
      </p>

      <h3>Investment, scholarships and responsibility with resources</h3>
      <p>
        Young people need to understand that scholarships, sponsorships, investments and opportunities are all resources that must be used responsibly. Nguyen AI Edu introduces the foundations of presenting an idea, building a scholarship portfolio, preparing a project, understanding responsibility to sponsors, understanding how an idea is evaluated and how a person builds trust through products, attitude and evidence. This content helps learners mature when approaching opportunities — not just seeking support but learning to be worthy of that support.
      </p>

      <h3>Freedom and career self-determination</h3>
      <p>
        Freedom does not come from not needing to do anything. Freedom comes from the capability to self-learn, self-do, self-adapt, self-create value and self-take responsibility. Nguyen AI Edu guides learners toward practical self-determination: knowing what they have, what they need to learn, what they can do, where they should begin and how to gradually create opportunities for themselves.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Online nationwide, in-person experience in Da Lat</h2>

      <p>
        Learners can join online from any province or city. This format suits students on summer break, recent graduates, job seekers, those working part-time or anyone who wants to learn outside working hours. Online activities can include lessons, materials, practice guidance, submissions, feedback, group discussions and product orientation.
      </p>

      <p>
        Alongside this, Nguyen AI Edu will organize some in-person activities in Da Lat, Lam Dong province when conditions allow. These can be meetups, group learning, project work, idea presentations, real-world experiences and connections with mentors, experts or a like-minded community.
      </p>

      <p>
        Da Lat is not just a location. Da Lat is a space suited for young people to slow down, observe more deeply, learn more seriously and begin ideas rooted in nature, locality, culture and people.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Scholarships and participation opportunities in July 2026</h2>

      <p>
        In July 2026, Nguyen AI Edu prioritizes the first scholarships for early registrants. Each program group may have 11 priority spots in the first round, depending on organizational capacity, number of applications and applicant fit.
      </p>

      <p>Those prioritized include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>people who carry the Nguyen surname;</li>
        <li>final-year students;</li>
        <li>recent graduates;</li>
        <li>young people looking for work;</li>
        <li>people who want part-time work during the summer;</li>
        <li>people who love artificial intelligence, technology and startups;</li>
        <li>people interested in personal brand, local brand, national brand;</li>
        <li>people who want to join education, media, business, community or digital product projects;</li>
        <li>people with a serious learning spirit and readiness to create products after the learning process.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        When the July 2026 scholarships have been awarded, learners can still choose from free programs that remain open, partially supported programs or paid courses on edu.nguyenai.net. Early registrants are reviewed first.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>What learners can gain</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on the program and level of participation, learners can gradually build:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>a personal capability portfolio;</li>
        <li>clearer career direction;</li>
        <li>a job search, part-time or internship plan;</li>
        <li>content products;</li>
        <li>a personal or project landing page;</li>
        <li>a structured startup idea presentation;</li>
        <li>a small verifiable project;</li>
        <li>a product tied to a locality or community;</li>
        <li>skills in using artificial intelligence for learning and work;</li>
        <li>the ability to present, work in teams and receive feedback;</li>
        <li>a foundation to continue learning more deeply or join suitable projects.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Results do not come from an introduction. Results come from the process of genuinely participating, practicing, correcting mistakes, refining and creating something visible.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Who should register early</h2>

      <p>
        You should register early if you are in one of these moments:
      </p>

      <p>
        You are about to graduate and want to prepare seriously for your first job. You just graduated and want to reshape your direction. You are looking for work but do not have a clear enough capability portfolio. You want part-time work but want that work to help you grow long-term. You love artificial intelligence and want to use it in learning, work and creativity. You want to build a personal brand or your own project. You are interested in startups but want to begin with method. You love Da Lat, Lam Dong, local brands, education, technology and Vietnamese values. You carry the Nguyen surname and want to join a learning, working and startup ecosystem with character.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>An invitation from Nguyen AI Edu</h2>

      <p>
        If you are looking for a more meaningful summer, start with one clear step.
      </p>

      <p>
        Learn a new capability. Make a small product. Rewrite your portfolio. Try joining a project. Meet like-minded people. Understand artificial intelligence by using it to create real results. Look back at where you live, your story, your possibilities and turn them into a direction with value.
      </p>

      <p>
        Nguyen AI Edu opens the summer 2026 program for young people who want to learn for real, do for real, become more self-directed and step into the future with their own capability.
      </p>

